By: Hermes
Glossary:
  - Term:
      - Cosmos
      - Kosmos
      - κόσμος
    Definition: Order, ornament, ordered universe (as Scott indicates).
---
Rightly is the Kosmos so named; for all things in it are wrought into an
ordered whole by the ... immutable necessity that rules in it, and by the
combining of the elements, and the fit disposal of all things that come into
being.
